FocusGroup -- third-party data notice
=====================================

Bundled dataset: anes_2024_personas

This package ships a small example dataset, `anes_2024_personas` (100 rows),
derived from the public release of the American National Election Studies (ANES)
2024 Time Series Study.

Source and citation
-------------------
American National Election Studies. 2025. ANES 2024 Time Series Study Full
Release [dataset and documentation]. August 8, 2025.
https://electionstudies.org/data-center/2024-time-series-study/

What is and is not included
---------------------------
- The dataset is a DERIVED product of the ANES public release: selected
  variables, decoded to their value labels, with demographics coarsened (age in
  bands, broad income and race or ethnicity categories, census region rather than
  state).
- It contains NO ANES respondent identifiers, NO granular geography, NO
  open-ended text, and NO restricted-use ANES variables.
- The 100 respondents were selected by diversity sampling for example coverage.
  The dataset is NOT a representative sample and carries no survey weights.
- Items concerning sexual orientation and gender identity are excluded.

ANES asks that derived datasets link back to the source dataset and that
publications cite ANES. The ANES is not responsible for the analyses or
interpretations presented here. ANES public-use data may be used and
redistributed in derived form with attribution; ANES restricted-use data and its
derivatives are not used in this package.
